If an attacker breaks through the first two layers of defense, next up in the defensive line are authentication and access control. It needs to add more complexity to the system so that the attacker whoâ€™s in the intranet wonâ€™t be able to do any lateral movement.</p>

<p>Enforcing strong password policies such as complexity, periodic changes, and two-factor authentication for critical systems are some simple measures to avoid lateral movement rather than using SSO. The API gateway should come into action to withhold any attacks here. It can provide the following key auth features to enforce API security.</p>

